WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.143 --> 00:00:03.458
Well, good evening.

00:00:06.240 --> 00:00:10.789
Thank you for joining us to look at the Christmas lights; I thought that was kind of fun.

00:00:10.789 --> 00:00:14.020
Paisley's been asking—we drive by and she says, 'Daddy, I want to go look at the lights.

00:00:14.020 --> 00:00:15.966
' I said, 'Okay, let's go look at the lights.

00:00:15.966 --> 00:00:19.570
' So, I thought, why not bring you all with us?

00:00:19.840 --> 00:00:21.660
Hopefully, you had a little fun.

00:00:21.660 --> 00:00:29.160
I know it was kind of quick, but if you don't move quick, sometimes you've just got a little bit of time left walking around.

00:00:29.160 --> 00:00:33.749
Megan was ready to go, so I thought I'd bring y'all along.

00:00:36.310 --> 00:00:42.800
When you go to the Oklahoma City Zoo Lights, they're the best; it is phenomenal.

00:00:42.800 --> 00:00:51.813
They have a huge display at the Oklahoma City Zoo, and we'll go over there and look at the lights sometimes and drive through their park.

00:00:52.227 --> 00:01:01.840
They've closed off roads where you can see the animals; they're making noises as you're looking at the lights, and it's pretty cool.

00:01:01.840 --> 00:01:05.199
It's probably one of my top favorite things to do, but it's pretty expensive.

00:01:05.199 --> 00:01:15.966
I think it's about $60 to go, and it only lasts about an hour, so you burn that money pretty quick.

00:01:18.766 --> 00:01:22.498
The hot chocolate's expensive, too, but it's something fun to do every once in a while.

00:01:23.810 --> 00:01:25.759
That's what we did tonight.

00:01:25.959 --> 00:01:27.669
I thought we'd come on and pray.

00:01:27.669 --> 00:01:40.151
Diana and I have been listening to Joyce again, and she's been talking about pride and things the Lord shapes when you're on that potter's wheel and the Lord's telling you, 'I want you to study this.

00:01:40.151 --> 00:01:41.119
I want you to keep going.

00:01:41.119 --> 00:01:43.360
I want you to come deeper with Me.

00:01:43.360 --> 00:01:50.510
' As I keep telling you all, the Lord said that in 2026, He's drawing the bride closer to His side.

00:01:50.510 --> 00:02:02.239
There are great days of shakings and awakenings coming, and things the Lord is about to do with the body of Christ in 2026.

00:02:02.239 --> 00:02:19.733
2025 was for warning, but the manifestations of what He's told me are coming in 2026 will be a wake-up call—a wake-up call concerning the signs of the times of the coming of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:02:32.920 --> 00:02:33.120
I say it over and over again.

00:02:33.120 --> 00:02:43.073
The Lord teaches me a lot about the love walk when people hurt or wound you, and you have to be quick to respond.

00:02:43.073 --> 00:02:47.691
I've said, 'Lord, what do you want me to do about this?

00:02:47.691 --> 00:02:49.862
How do you want me to handle this?

00:02:49.862 --> 00:02:52.893
I'm really ticked off.

00:02:52.893 --> 00:02:58.140
' And He says, 'Brandon, walk in love.

00:03:00.280 --> 00:03:00.640
Love never fails.

00:03:00.640 --> 00:03:04.090
' I say, 'They're wrong, Lord.

00:03:04.090 --> 00:03:05.760
This is wrong.

00:03:15.200 --> 00:03:15.404
I'm upset about this.

00:03:15.404 --> 00:03:18.860
' But love takes no account of a suffered wrong.

00:03:26.959 --> 00:03:27.291
Remember that.

00:03:27.291 --> 00:03:39.139
If you want to walk higher with the fire, you must learn to walk in love, even when people do you wrong.

00:03:49.661 --> 00:03:50.053
The first reaction is always where they're really at.

00:04:00.439 --> 00:04:00.639
Is it a quick repentance?

00:04:00.639 --> 00:04:04.240
Is it an excuse for how it happened?

00:04:04.240 --> 00:04:07.819
Is it 'I'm sorry,' or is it quick?

00:04:11.360 --> 00:04:11.580
That's why you can pinpoint people.

00:04:11.580 --> 00:04:22.479
But the Lord tells me that regardless of how people act or what they say, you are required to walk in love, for that's where the greater glory is.

00:04:22.479 --> 00:04:26.604
Remember what the angel said when he visited the other night?

00:04:26.604 --> 00:04:30.240
The angel with the opal armor.

00:04:44.809 --> 00:04:45.067
The glory of the Lord filled my home so strongly.

00:04:45.582 --> 00:04:49.874
It lasted for over a day after he visited.

00:04:59.190 --> 00:04:59.460
I've said before, 'I don't talk to angels,' but the angel had a word.

00:04:59.460 --> 00:05:03.246
He spoke: 'The Lord has sent me to give you a message.

00:05:14.284 --> 00:05:14.595
You want to know the key to the greater glory?

00:05:15.218 --> 00:05:28.937
You want to know how you're going to walk in the manifestations in these last days, how you'll be a frontrunner instead of the one tagging behind?

00:05:28.937 --> 00:05:33.668
' We say, 'Well, that's pride.

00:05:33.668 --> 00:05:44.411
' No, there are going to be trailblazers and there are going to be those following behind.

00:05:54.356 --> 00:05:54.773
I want to be walking with the King.

00:05:54.773 --> 00:06:01.120
When He's coming back and we're riding with Him, I want my horse to be on the front row.

00:06:01.466 --> 00:06:04.940
I want to hear Him say, 'Brandon, well done, son.

00:06:04.940 --> 00:06:13.804
' No matter how much people hurt or offend you, or how much they wound you in life—whether they are close to you or not—words hurt.

00:06:13.804 --> 00:06:15.951
People hurt people.

00:06:15.951 --> 00:06:20.986
It's not always intentional; sometimes people do it ignorantly.

00:06:37.600 --> 00:06:37.999
But I'm telling you, your first response must always be love.

00:06:37.999 --> 00:06:44.125
Sometimes you have to take a step back.

00:06:48.354 --> 00:06:49.039
In my own situations, I've noticed I sometimes freak out and say things.

00:06:50.960 --> 00:06:54.560
When I get wounded, I have a tendency to explode, and the Lord says, 'Draw back.

00:06:54.560 --> 00:06:58.183
' It's like a horse you pull back.

00:06:58.183 --> 00:06:59.1000
What's your first reaction?

00:06:59.1000 --> 00:07:09.220
Mine is usually anger, and I'll say a lot with my mouth, but the Lord says, 'Draw back.

00:07:15.439 --> 00:07:15.679
Love never fails, Brandon.

00:07:15.919 --> 00:07:20.149
Your job is to always walk in love.

00:07:20.149 --> 00:07:29.599
' When that angel visited and said, 'What is going to bring in the greater glory is a love foundation—your love walk.

00:07:29.599 --> 00:07:31.199
Where are you with your love?

00:07:31.199 --> 00:07:36.309
' It's the second time I've had angels talk to me like that.

00:07:36.309 --> 00:07:41.315
One was a couple of years ago on Valentine's Day.

00:07:41.315 --> 00:07:42.560
It was amazing.

00:07:42.560 --> 00:07:50.800
A lot of people say, 'I don't go with all that,' but it's still about love.

00:08:01.160 --> 00:08:01.866
Love never fails; God is love.

00:08:17.727 --> 00:08:18.015
The Lord said to me then that the thing he needs to know the most—what he'll be judged on the most—is: how did he treat his brethren?

00:08:18.015 --> 00:08:21.074
How did he walk in love?

00:08:21.074 --> 00:08:25.720
How do you walk in love toward your wife, your husband, and your kids?

00:08:25.720 --> 00:08:35.549
When people wound you, you don't have to allow them to keep hurting you, but your reaction to them is love.

00:08:35.549 --> 00:08:40.503
Now, trust is earned; I want you to understand that.

00:08:51.299 --> 00:08:51.519
It doesn't mean you trust everybody or let everyone into your circle.

00:08:51.519 --> 00:09:01.451
In fact, the first thing the Lord told me when I started this ministry was, 'Trust no one.

00:09:01.451 --> 00:09:05.129
Don't allow people in your inner circle, Brandon.

00:09:18.480 --> 00:09:18.800
There are things I will call you to do and say where you're not allowed to have friends.

00:09:18.800 --> 00:09:22.228
You'll be separated unto Me to say the hard things.

00:09:22.228 --> 00:09:38.834
There will be a target on you in the natural, and you will be required to take communion and fellowship with Me, and walk in love with your wife and kids.

00:09:38.834 --> 00:09:55.187
' I've learned even with family it's not always the easiest thing to do because they're not always going to 'get' you, and it's not required for them to get you.

00:09:56.107 --> 00:09:59.059
You are obedient unto God.

00:10:01.440 --> 00:10:03.920
The Lord even says to me regarding the emails we get, 'Fear God, not man.

00:10:03.920 --> 00:10:05.337
Fear Me, not man.

00:10:05.337 --> 00:10:08.640
Don't worry about what they're saying about you.

00:10:08.640 --> 00:10:13.967
Draw close to My side and walk with Me in this end-time harvest.

00:10:13.967 --> 00:10:18.868
Walk with Me and I'll use you greatly and mightily.

00:10:18.868 --> 00:10:26.859
' They won't understand why you're accelerating so quickly, but it's not for them.

00:10:26.859 --> 00:10:28.239
Keep humble.

00:10:44.560 --> 00:10:44.800
Keep your flesh under and keep the love walk straight.

00:10:52.790 --> 00:10:53.240
I had an opportunity this weekend to be really ticked off at some things.

00:10:55.964 --> 00:11:01.040
I'm telling you, I haven't been that mad in a long time, to the point where I was trembling.

00:11:05.493 --> 00:11:07.316
I asked, 'Lord, what do you want me to do about all this mess?

00:11:07.316 --> 00:11:09.279
' He said, "Walk in love.

00:11:09.279 --> 00:11:14.320
" I said, "Are you telling me to walk in love?

00:11:14.320 --> 00:11:17.164
I'm going to go off.

00:11:32.799 --> 00:11:32.959
What do you want me to do, Lord?

00:11:40.360 --> 00:11:41.590
" "Walk in love.

00:11:41.590 --> 00:11:44.400
" I said, "Walk in love.

00:11:44.800 --> 00:11:57.623
" The key to the greater glory, son, is even whenever you feel somebody has done you wrong—and they did—is to walk in love.

00:11:57.623 --> 00:12:04.274
Regardless of the excuses they try to make afterwards, wrong is wrong and right is right.

00:12:04.274 --> 00:12:11.370
It doesn't matter what their response is; your response is love.

00:12:32.800 --> 00:12:33.080
And that's what he said to me.

00:12:33.080 --> 00:12:39.240
And I said, "That's hard for my flesh to hear.

00:12:46.102 --> 00:12:48.159
" I'm screaming inside, you know, and it's like that.

00:12:48.159 --> 00:12:49.760
Diana is upset.

00:12:49.760 --> 00:12:51.416
D is crying.

00:12:51.416 --> 00:12:59.040
And what do you do whenever you're wounded so deep by people that you love and trust?

00:12:59.520 --> 00:13:00.171
You walk in love.

00:13:07.977 --> 00:13:08.566
And that's why the Lord said, "It doesn't mean you have to keep planted there.

00:13:08.566 --> 00:13:15.376
It doesn't mean you have to keep doing these things.

00:13:15.376 --> 00:13:16.309
It's your choice.

00:13:16.309 --> 00:13:23.440
It's your choice if you want to walk in the greater glory.

00:13:23.940 --> 00:13:25.440
I will use you mightily.

00:13:25.440 --> 00:13:26.987
But God is love.

00:13:26.987 --> 00:13:33.154
It's not what he does; it's who he is.

00:13:35.959 --> 00:13:40.631
" And if you want to walk by his side, even whenever it's something innocent or not innocent, it doesn't matter.

00:13:40.631 --> 00:13:43.387
I'm not looking at them; I'm looking at him.

00:13:43.387 --> 00:13:44.720
I'm staying vertical.

00:13:44.937 --> 00:13:50.320
And you must learn to stay vertical in these days ahead.

00:13:52.239 --> 00:14:00.320
The Lord showed me as I was walking even at Rhema tonight, he said, "You must learn to stay vertical.

00:14:10.687 --> 00:14:12.512
It's not always going to be easy because the devil wants you to go horizontal and look at everybody else and what they're doing.

00:14:12.512 --> 00:14:14.969
" But what about them?

00:14:14.969 --> 00:14:16.699
How come them?

00:14:25.733 --> 00:14:26.026
And he said, "No, stay vertical.

00:14:26.026 --> 00:14:28.607
Who cares about what they're doing?

00:14:30.192 --> 00:14:32.594
Your job is to be the branch and stay on the vine.

00:14:32.594 --> 00:14:36.434
Your job is to keep looking at me.

00:14:36.434 --> 00:14:42.410
" Because if you look at what's around you, your pride sets in and you start thinking, "Woe is me.

00:14:42.910 --> 00:14:58.230
" You start singing a sad song, and everybody has a sad song they can sing about how people do you wrong or how people might have not done it intentionally or whatever.

00:14:58.230 --> 00:14:59.669
It doesn't matter.

00:14:59.669 --> 00:15:03.336
Your job is to always maintain love.

00:15:03.336 --> 00:15:12.810
Now, love doesn't mean you have to keep doing the same thing over and over again and allowing people to hurt you.

00:15:14.524 --> 00:15:17.750
The lesson is: don't allow people in your inner circle.

00:15:17.750 --> 00:15:29.976
I've learned a lot, and I'm trying to teach you all something because Brandon and I have learned a lot as we walk down the road.

00:15:29.976 --> 00:15:36.920
This has not been an easy journey for me, but I'm learning I want to walk with him.

00:15:36.920 --> 00:15:42.982
I always know when I've messed up because that anointing lifts off me.

00:15:42.982 --> 00:15:46.433
But he said, "Be angry and sin not.

00:15:46.433 --> 00:15:58.891
" He said that because I don't have much of a filter sometimes when people tick me off and I just go, and that's the way he said, "Be angry and sin not.

00:16:03.120 --> 00:16:03.920
" It's okay to be angry, but don't sin in your anger.

00:16:03.920 --> 00:16:12.639
Does that make sense what I'm telling y'all?

00:16:12.639 --> 00:16:25.279
So that's the lesson I've been learning in the last 48 hours: Be angry, sin not, walk in love.

00:16:32.000 --> 00:16:33.280
You must learn to walk in love; it's the only way to the greater glory.

00:16:33.280 --> 00:16:34.629
Remember the angel.

00:16:44.749 --> 00:16:48.889
He says it's always those life lessons; that's how we're going to walk with him.

00:16:48.889 --> 00:16:54.940
Even whenever people talk trash about you or run you down, your job is always to stay on the love side.

00:16:54.940 --> 00:16:59.700
Remember that because you're going to be tested just like Brandon is tested.

00:17:01.280 --> 00:17:01.839
But hopefully, you can learn from our mistakes.

00:17:01.839 --> 00:17:08.604
So be very careful who you let in your inner courts.

00:17:25.830 --> 00:17:26.132
Be careful who you let in your inner tent.

00:17:26.132 --> 00:17:28.354
Be careful who's influencing you.

00:17:28.354 --> 00:17:34.057
Watch who's speaking into your life.

00:17:34.057 --> 00:17:36.920
Watch where you're feeding.

00:17:36.920 --> 00:17:43.474
Make sure you're growing and you're going from glory to glory.

00:17:43.474 --> 00:17:47.584
It's your responsibility to monitor your thermostat.

00:17:47.584 --> 00:17:52.583
If your thermostat is cold, check your thermostat spiritually.

00:17:54.023 --> 00:17:57.931
You say, "I'm going to a church that doesn't feed me.

00:18:17.440 --> 00:18:18.080
I'm hanging around people who pull me down.

00:18:18.080 --> 00:18:21.280
" Check your thermostat.

00:18:21.280 --> 00:18:31.325
There are many of you that say, "Well, I'm married into an unequally yoked marriage, Brandon.

00:18:33.519 --> 00:18:33.719
What should I do?

00:18:33.719 --> 00:18:46.784
" Well, you shouldn't have done that in the first place, but now that you're in it, you don't get a divorce.

00:18:47.455 --> 00:18:49.619
You're in covenant.

00:18:50.440 --> 00:18:58.680
So you walk it out in love and you pray for your spouse.

00:19:13.307 --> 00:19:13.640
The Bible says, "Don't be unequally yoked with unbelievers.

00:19:13.640 --> 00:19:15.600
" It's your choice.

00:19:15.600 --> 00:19:22.620
Now, if you got saved during that marriage, you keep interceding.

00:19:23.726 --> 00:19:25.440
You fast, you pray, you anoint.

00:19:25.440 --> 00:19:33.840
I would take olive oil—this is what I got from Billy Burke—and I'm telling you what, solid people, Billy Burke.

00:19:43.200 --> 00:19:43.600
You anoint their pillow with oil.

00:19:44.986 --> 00:19:53.350
You anoint them at night, and they don't even have to know you're doing it.

00:19:53.350 --> 00:20:05.253
Maybe they wake up in the morning; you put a little bit on that pillow and you anoint it.

00:20:05.253 --> 00:20:13.360
And I pray over them over and over and over again.

00:20:13.360 --> 00:20:16.008
Make your prayer petition for 2026.

00:20:17.679 --> 00:20:19.777
That's what I tried to teach you all last night.

00:20:19.777 --> 00:20:25.010
We always write the vision down of everything we're believing for every single year.

00:20:25.010 --> 00:20:29.373
Whether it's a house, we write it down.

00:20:29.373 --> 00:20:42.000
It may be something so big that you know that God is the only one that can bring it to pass.

00:20:52.666 --> 00:20:53.412
And you go, "How is that even possible?

00:20:53.412 --> 00:21:00.320
This is not possible by man's standard, but it's possible through God.

00:21:00.320 --> 00:21:05.097
" So you have to write your vision down.

00:21:05.097 --> 00:21:06.640
Put it down before you.

00:21:06.640 --> 00:21:09.830
Put your love scriptures, put whatever you've got.

00:21:09.830 --> 00:21:11.210
Write the vision down.

00:21:11.210 --> 00:21:21.109
Make sure you keep that in priority and put it on a mirror, on your car visor, or by your bed where you sleep on your nightstand.

00:21:27.166 --> 00:21:27.394
Make sure you have that as something that's always in front of your face.

00:21:27.394 --> 00:21:30.702
You have to keep the vision in front of you.

00:21:30.702 --> 00:21:43.253
That's why I try to tell people all the time: if you don't have big house mentality, go drive in the big neighborhoods and get that inside of you so that you can start thinking bigger.

00:21:43.253 --> 00:21:46.523
Poverty thinks poverty; rich thinks rich.

00:21:46.523 --> 00:21:47.919
Does that make sense?

00:21:47.919 --> 00:21:57.749
If you think like a winner, you don't go around a losing baseball team or a losing football team and get winning inside of you.

00:21:57.749 --> 00:22:02.749
If they're always losing, loser is going to be inside of you.

00:22:02.749 --> 00:22:06.114
You've got to get around a winner.

00:22:06.114 --> 00:22:09.160
Go watch somebody who's a champion.

00:22:09.160 --> 00:22:16.613
You've got to get that inside of you so that it changes you from the inside out.

00:22:16.613 --> 00:22:21.640
Add the Word to it, but get a vision.

00:22:21.640 --> 00:22:29.692
Get an inward vision of who you are in Christ and know that God's created you to be more than a conqueror.

00:22:32.559 --> 00:22:36.160
You are not made to be a 'just barely getting by' person.

00:22:37.039 --> 00:22:41.656
And maybe you're almost at the championship game and then you lose.

00:22:41.656 --> 00:22:46.690
Well, you learn from the losing and you get better the next year.

00:22:47.949 --> 00:22:53.1000
There is a place in God that the devil does not go when you're underneath that umbrella of the anointing.

00:22:53.1000 --> 00:23:01.632
You must learn to abide in love and abide in the glory of the Lord, even whenever your flesh does not want to.

00:23:01.632 --> 00:23:06.388
There are days whenever I just go, "Oh!

00:23:06.388 --> 00:23:13.200
" Like I said, I want to pull my hair out, and it's already pulled out.

00:23:13.200 --> 00:23:19.211
I'm trying to tell you all it's something Brandon's walking through, too.

00:23:19.211 --> 00:23:27.1000
But I so want that when I get on the other side, I say, "Jesus, I did everything I could.

00:23:37.039 --> 00:23:37.399
I sure tried.

00:23:38.479 --> 00:23:43.627
" I don't want to say, "Well, I didn't leave it all on the table.

00:23:43.627 --> 00:23:44.738
I wasn't all in.

00:23:45.236 --> 00:24:03.400
" I think a lot of people might have regrets, ladies and gentlemen, but it's what you do with the time and the effort that you've been given.

00:24:03.400 --> 00:24:10.810
I came across a guy that was really ripped.

00:24:13.340 --> 00:24:34.106
He had muscles on muscles, and it challenges you because you look at him and go, "Wow, he has the same hours in a day as I have, but he's really trim and fit and he looks good, and then here I am.

00:24:36.571 --> 00:24:36.949
" But where are you spiritually?

00:24:53.550 --> 00:24:53.860
I try to mirror myself off of Jesus, but at the same time, I'm going, "Where are people spiritually?

00:24:53.860 --> 00:24:55.942
" Where are people physically?

00:24:59.600 --> 00:25:07.859
I know I need to do better with my flesh, but I'm not satisfied with where I am spiritually either.

00:25:08.730 --> 00:25:09.310
I want more.

00:25:13.399 --> 00:25:13.779
I want to stand with Him.

00:25:19.022 --> 00:25:25.360
And the only way you're going to do that is to act like Jesus and be more like Him.

00:25:41.120 --> 00:25:41.307
And what did Jesus do, even whenever they were spitting on Him?

00:25:41.307 --> 00:25:44.420
Sometimes the best answer is no answer at all.

00:25:44.420 --> 00:25:56.759
Sometimes walking in love—whenever people are wanting a comment from you, wanting you to respond—sometimes to walk in love is not to give an answer at all.

00:25:56.759 --> 00:25:58.559
Just be still.

00:25:58.559 --> 00:26:04.019
Jesus didn't respond to it; He got quiet before them.

00:26:04.019 --> 00:26:09.520
They are the accusers of the brethren, the accusers of the palace.

00:26:09.520 --> 00:26:13.303
'Hey, what do you say to this?

00:26:13.303 --> 00:26:14.880
' Silence.

00:26:14.880 --> 00:26:17.109
'They're accusing you.

00:26:25.588 --> 00:26:25.896
They want to put you to death.

00:26:25.896 --> 00:26:26.823
' Silence.

00:26:26.823 --> 00:26:30.844
So, His example is that not everything requires a reaction.

00:26:30.844 --> 00:26:32.533
I'm learning that too.

00:26:32.533 --> 00:26:34.709
Sometimes no words is a good thing.

00:26:35.947 --> 00:26:37.120
We're all a work in progress.

00:26:45.159 --> 00:26:45.409
We're all learning.

00:26:45.409 --> 00:26:52.799
But I want to teach you all as much as what I'm learning, especially today and yesterday.

00:26:52.799 --> 00:26:54.400
Walk in love.

00:26:54.400 --> 00:26:55.700
Walk in love.

00:26:55.700 --> 00:26:57.333
Love never fails.

00:27:06.891 --> 00:27:07.246
You either have it or you don't.

00:27:07.246 --> 00:27:12.844
Either you're a believing believer or you're not.

00:27:12.844 --> 00:27:17.190
That was 17 minutes—that's not too bad for that part.

00:27:20.204 --> 00:27:23.875
I could have probably said more, but I try to save your time.

00:27:27.640 --> 00:27:27.869
And even reading Diana—she's a firecracker, too.

00:27:39.700 --> 00:27:39.970
But I tell you, listening...

00:27:39.970 --> 00:27:57.120
because the Lord told us, because we're talking about pride and Leviathan and the pride behind it and the spirits that try to be sneaky and you think you're humble.

00:27:57.120 --> 00:27:59.039
But you know what?

00:28:01.691 --> 00:28:01.943
This is something else.

00:28:05.420 --> 00:28:05.720
People say, 'Braden, you're humble.

00:28:05.720 --> 00:28:08.800
' 'Boy, you're humble, Brandon.

00:28:08.800 --> 00:28:13.840
' People say that all the time.

00:28:13.840 --> 00:28:16.612
Either you are or you're not.

00:28:16.612 --> 00:28:23.020
There's no pretending with humility.

00:28:23.020 --> 00:28:32.480
It's displayed by a reaction of love when you realize that it's not you doing something.

00:28:44.939 --> 00:28:45.549
You don't have to convince yourself.

00:28:45.549 --> 00:28:48.799
Either you are or you're not.

00:28:48.799 --> 00:28:56.959
I don't have to walk around and try to display humility.

00:28:56.959 --> 00:28:59.360
Either it is or it's not.

00:28:59.360 --> 00:29:01.280
'Well, Brandon, you're humble.

00:29:01.280 --> 00:29:06.000
Brandon, you're prideful.

00:29:06.000 --> 00:29:10.030
Brandon, this whatever.

00:29:10.030 --> 00:29:14.559
' Either you are or you're not.

00:29:14.559 --> 00:29:15.952
You cannot fake humility.

00:29:15.952 --> 00:29:25.110
Either it's you, either it's Jesus Christ in you, or it's not.

00:29:25.120 --> 00:29:30.429
But I don't have to vocalize it.

00:29:30.429 --> 00:29:36.853
That's why I don't ever say I try to be whatever, because I know.

00:29:36.853 --> 00:29:45.200
If you look at my resume, you know Brandon doesn't have what it takes in the natural.

00:29:45.200 --> 00:29:47.253
Do you understand?

00:29:47.253 --> 00:29:50.302
Brandon is solely dependent upon Jesus.

00:29:50.888 --> 00:29:51.893
I don't have much education.

00:29:51.893 --> 00:29:54.720
People say, 'Brandon, don't knock yourself.

00:29:54.720 --> 00:29:56.987
' No, I'm stating a fact.

00:29:56.987 --> 00:30:00.860
That's not me trying to be humble; that's just stating a fact.

00:30:10.840 --> 00:30:11.200
I am flat-out nothing without Jesus Christ or my education.

00:30:11.200 --> 00:30:17.639
When you can barely read and write...

00:30:17.639 --> 00:30:23.733
things that I do read well, I've read probably a thousand times or I've studied it.

00:30:31.864 --> 00:30:32.200
If it's raw, like reading those articles that Braden puts up, you can take it to the bank: I'm going to be embarrassed.

00:30:32.200 --> 00:30:33.039
But I learned...

00:30:33.039 --> 00:30:50.360
even whenever I played games at Christmas time with people at youth parties, I would be the one hiding in the back because I was so embarrassed to play those games because they had to read and I couldn't read.

00:30:59.989 --> 00:31:01.279
I remember sitting in there and they would play those games at Christmas time and they said, 'Braden, do you want to play?

00:31:01.279 --> 00:31:11.909
' I said, 'Oh, no.

00:31:11.919 --> 00:31:14.640
I'm not interested,' and I'd make up an excuse.

00:31:14.640 --> 00:31:19.003
But really, the bottom line is I wanted to play with all my heart.

00:31:19.759 --> 00:31:56.898
I wanted to play with all my heart, but I was so ashamed that I was a teenager and I couldn't read that I didn't want to embarrass myself in front of all the high school kids.

00:31:56.898 --> 00:32:02.720
So, I would go and do something else and talk to the adults.

00:32:02.720 --> 00:32:34.939
A lot of times I'd go in and talk the Word to the mother of the party or the father because I was so ashamed that I couldn't do what the other kids were doing.

00:32:34.939 --> 00:32:37.900
That's what I developed; it was a defense mechanism.

00:32:37.900 --> 00:32:46.719
A lot of that came out of just a lot of pain.

00:32:54.377 --> 00:32:55.543
And even whenever I was a janitor and cleaning for all these years, it was the mechanism of rejection.

00:32:55.543 --> 00:33:01.264
There was so much rejection going through a lot of pastors.

00:33:07.937 --> 00:33:12.760
You know, it's like with us—nobody really cares truly about you.

00:33:12.760 --> 00:33:20.799
If I were still the janitor, nobody would give a crap.

00:33:20.799 --> 00:33:28.933
But because I have a million people following me now, people try to reach out to you.

00:33:28.933 --> 00:33:39.055
But really, the bottom line is, if you were still the janitor, they wouldn't even look your direction.

00:33:39.055 --> 00:33:41.600
They don't give a crap about you.

00:33:41.600 --> 00:33:42.427
Remember that.

00:33:52.126 --> 00:33:52.480
It's about Jesus inside of you.

00:33:52.480 --> 00:33:58.702
And when He exalts you and promotes you, people look your way.

00:33:58.702 --> 00:34:02.099
I was the janitor all the time.

00:34:02.099 --> 00:34:07.440
I went there and I cleaned 90 toilets two or three times a week.

00:34:07.720 --> 00:34:12.773
And even then, they said, 'Go in there and clean your bathrooms.

00:34:13.075 --> 00:34:17.240
You aren't going to touch nobody and lay hands on anybody.

00:34:17.240 --> 00:34:23.582
' But the glory was on my hands even then.

00:34:26.720 --> 00:34:33.740
And I could lay hands on people and the power of God would hit them and cancer would fall off their face.

00:34:33.740 --> 00:34:39.339
I'll never forget this lady walked up to me while I was vacuuming the floor.

00:34:39.339 --> 00:34:49.679
Her boy was diagnosed with stage four cancer and she came up to me while I was cleaning the church and she said, 'I've heard...

00:34:49.679 --> 00:34:50.708
we're desperate.

00:34:54.107 --> 00:34:59.359
There's nobody in this church that knows how to pray for anybody, but could you please pray for my son?

00:34:59.359 --> 00:35:03.040
He starts chemo in a couple of days.

00:35:03.040 --> 00:35:06.120
Can you lay hands on him?

00:35:06.120 --> 00:35:12.509
Do you see this knot on the side of his face?

00:35:12.509 --> 00:35:15.760
It's the size of an egg.

00:35:15.760 --> 00:35:18.810
Can you pray for it?

00:35:18.810 --> 00:35:20.613
' I said, 'Yes.

00:35:20.613 --> 00:35:27.050
' So, I shut the door because I didn't want to get in trouble.

00:35:34.400 --> 00:35:34.613
I opened the door and I said, 'Come on in here, buddy.

00:35:34.613 --> 00:35:41.010
' I said, 'In the name of Jesus Christ, I cursed that cancer and told it to go.

00:35:41.010 --> 00:35:45.940
' Three days later, she came back to the church crying.

00:35:45.940 --> 00:35:48.880
She said, 'Brandon, look, it's gone.

00:35:48.880 --> 00:35:55.520
' Not by what Brandon did, but by what Jesus did through Brandon.

00:35:59.209 --> 00:36:04.480
And when you realize 'Christ in me, Christ in me,' that little boy's life—he didn't have to go to chemo.

00:36:04.480 --> 00:36:06.827
They went back to the doctor.

00:36:06.827 --> 00:36:13.620
They went back to the doctor and the doctor said, 'What happened?

00:36:13.620 --> 00:36:23.510
' She told him and he tried to make up an excuse that it wasn't cancer.

00:36:23.510 --> 00:36:25.336
I thought it was funny.

00:36:25.336 --> 00:36:27.493
I said, 'Isn't Jesus wonderful?

00:36:27.493 --> 00:36:29.900
' Do you understand?

00:36:29.900 --> 00:36:36.680
Jesus will meet you where you are and He loves you.

00:36:36.680 --> 00:36:51.439
But when you're going through the valley with all this pressure, like I'm learning, you're not important until you have a following in the world's eyes.

00:36:51.439 --> 00:36:55.244
But Jesus saw you as important when you were scrubbing poop.

00:36:55.244 --> 00:36:56.436
Do you understand?

00:36:59.482 --> 00:37:10.151
And so I don't get into all of the political stuff even when I'm invited to the White House.

00:37:10.151 --> 00:37:13.920
It's all a show pony.

00:37:13.920 --> 00:37:25.989
I refuse to be show ponies because you weren't there when I was a janitor and you didn't care then.

00:37:25.989 --> 00:37:33.680
So I realize the bigger the platform, the bigger the call what God has put inside of me.

00:37:33.680 --> 00:37:42.140
And regardless of how much God promotes Brandon Biggs, He always says, 'Stay the janitor, Brandon.

00:37:42.140 --> 00:37:45.817
Don't ever forget where I brought you from.

00:37:45.817 --> 00:38:05.200
' Never forget it, for you're about to enter into the second phase of your ministry and healing is going to fall out of your hands and cancer is going to dry up on a greater scale.

00:38:16.480 --> 00:38:16.684
The fire is going to drive out sickness like you wouldn't believe, son.

00:38:16.684 --> 00:38:20.933
But that's going to be the time whenever your ministry really takes off.

00:38:20.933 --> 00:38:24.320
Remember this and always keep small in your own eyes.

00:38:30.907 --> 00:38:33.040
I was out doing my yard work and He always tells me that: 'Remember to stay small in your own eyes.

00:38:33.040 --> 00:38:37.383
' And it was a flattering thing even this week.

00:38:42.420 --> 00:38:42.760
I was sent the videos of the Christmas party tonight with President Trump.

00:38:44.639 --> 00:38:46.274
And I got to see Billy Graham—the son spoke.

00:38:52.400 --> 00:38:52.620
I got to see another man.

00:38:52.620 --> 00:38:56.079
I don't know who he was, Benny Johnson.

00:38:56.079 --> 00:38:57.1000
These other people were there.

00:38:57.1000 --> 00:39:07.733
They all went to the Christmas party tonight, the one that I said I didn't want to go to.

00:39:20.690 --> 00:39:22.200
I was very excited that they sent me the videos and I got to hear what President Trump said to the people, saying we're going to say Christmas again as a nation.

00:39:22.200 --> 00:39:51.105
He said a lot of things that were really cool about the Christians and was saying that we're bringing religion back or Christianity back and the things that he was saying from the platform, talking to all those pastors who were invited to come to the Christmas party tonight.

00:39:51.105 --> 00:40:05.268
So, I thought it was really neat that they shared with me what was said.

00:40:05.268 --> 00:40:11.867
I was excited that they included me even after I rejected the invitation.

00:40:11.867 --> 00:40:14.040
But I thought, you know what?

00:40:22.619 --> 00:40:23.249
Jesus is wonderful.

00:40:23.249 --> 00:40:32.080
Even when they say, "Hey, next time you will be here.

00:40:32.080 --> 00:40:34.799
Next time we want you here.

00:40:34.799 --> 00:40:39.133
Next time you will come to these parties.

00:40:39.133 --> 00:40:41.211
We want you here.

00:40:41.211 --> 00:40:46.023
" I take it as whatever, you know?

00:40:46.023 --> 00:41:15.302
All I want is just to sit on my little couch here and to teach you all how to pray.

00:41:15.302 --> 00:41:57.276
If you don't understand the authority of the believer, if you don't understand who you are, you're not going to make it in the days ahead.

00:41:57.276 --> 00:42:17.600
I say this not to scare you, but to prepare you.

00:43:10.480 --> 00:43:10.860
You must understand Psalms 91.

00:43:12.660 --> 00:43:13.650
You must understand Psalms 23.

00:43:26.949 --> 00:43:27.303
You must understand the authority of the believer.

00:43:27.303 --> 00:43:32.720
I always try to talk about Sister Billy.

00:43:32.720 --> 00:43:37.670
She's been such a friend.

00:44:17.467 --> 00:44:48.891
I want you to understand you must understand the authority of the believer, and you read these little books like this and you get that authority down inside you.

00:45:05.497 --> 00:45:21.554
I didn't realize how many people have no idea about who they are in Christ and you must get this down inside of you.

00:45:22.743 --> 00:45:29.500
You must, and she would even tell you to walk in love.

00:45:32.860 --> 00:45:38.160
So always stay small as much as God promotes you.

00:45:49.928 --> 00:45:50.213
And there'll be a lot of you that you've been the janitor just like Brandon Biggs.

00:46:00.057 --> 00:46:03.173
And you'll look back at your life and you'll pinch yourself at what God's about to do because all to Jesus we surrender.

00:46:03.173 --> 00:46:06.039
All to him I humbly give.

00:46:06.039 --> 00:46:08.125
Do you understand?

00:46:08.125 --> 00:46:10.640
Diana was clerical.

00:46:19.280 --> 00:46:19.620
I entered in all the offerings.

00:46:20.300 --> 00:46:21.660
I counted the offerings.

00:46:27.067 --> 00:46:33.098
I did it all for years, counting the offerings and entering in your tithe and offerings at the megachurch we worked at.

00:46:43.760 --> 00:46:44.800
And we learned a lot.

00:46:44.800 --> 00:46:50.684
But never turn your nose up to small beginnings.

00:46:50.684 --> 00:47:11.420
So because one day maybe they'll call you to want to go to the White House and maybe you will say no, maybe you'll say yes, but it's all about him.

00:47:25.653 --> 00:47:34.999
You know, all the conferences that I've been invited to to speak to tens of thousands of people on a regular basis, I'm going to say, well, it has been all of them, haven't it?

00:47:34.999 --> 00:47:38.599
All of them I have said no to.

00:47:38.599 --> 00:47:41.885
It's not funny.

00:47:53.063 --> 00:47:53.269
I just don't, I'm not into it.

00:47:53.269 --> 00:47:54.613
It's just real.

00:47:55.236 --> 00:48:04.090
And I had to say to myself, you know, well, I have to say I spoke at Sister Billy's tent thing.

00:48:04.090 --> 00:48:07.260
Yeah, and I like that.

00:48:17.700 --> 00:48:17.920
That was fun.

00:48:17.920 --> 00:48:25.177
But it wasn't on the internet, so I felt good about it.

00:48:25.177 --> 00:48:33.589
You don't have to worry about it because what if you mess up?

00:48:33.589 --> 00:48:45.577
What if you say something really stupid and it's on there and you're not in control of the video?

00:48:45.577 --> 00:48:49.200
But to me, it's just like whatever.

00:48:49.200 --> 00:48:53.699
So, all 4,040 of you, you got my little lesson today about walking in love.

00:48:53.699 --> 00:48:55.900
I was going to bring in Diana.

00:49:01.839 --> 00:49:02.079
So, if she wants to pray with us, I told her I'll talk for a second.

00:49:02.079 --> 00:49:02.800
Oh, 4,040.

00:49:11.257 --> 00:49:11.462
Here, move that camera up a little bit.

00:49:11.462 --> 00:49:12.800
Let me get her.

00:49:12.800 --> 00:49:22.880
I want to see if she can pray because I talk and then I let her come in because she's really busy.

00:49:28.040 --> 00:49:28.470
You all keep her busy.

00:49:28.470 --> 00:49:34.240
She is busy doing the emails, man.

00:49:34.240 --> 00:49:35.680
We're a three-man army.

00:49:35.680 --> 00:49:38.719
Braden does the editing and all the stuff.

00:49:38.719 --> 00:49:52.319
Diana does the emails and talking to the people and getting all that done, sending out the Bibles, and then Brandon tries to keep himself full and talking to you all.

00:49:54.559 --> 00:49:55.710
And so it's pretty crazy, but all right.

00:49:55.710 --> 00:49:56.400
Hold on.

00:49:56.400 --> 00:50:07.300
Who I was going to ask this question, I don't know if you all, I tried to do this poll.

00:50:07.300 --> 00:50:14.315
A lot of these people don't know who Kathryn Kuhlman is.

00:50:14.315 --> 00:50:20.957
So I did a poll last time.

00:50:37.839 --> 00:50:38.102
I think like 30% didn't know who she was, which is amazing to me.

00:50:41.299 --> 00:50:41.569
I think it was like 30 to 40%.

00:50:41.569 --> 00:50:43.040
So, it was pretty high.

00:50:43.040 --> 00:50:43.400
Hi.

00:50:43.400 --> 00:50:47.154
She probably is cooking right now.

00:50:50.071 --> 00:50:50.382
I don't know.

00:50:50.382 --> 00:50:50.693
Here, let me see.

00:50:51.315 --> 00:50:55.760
I was going to say, do you know who Billy Graham was?

00:50:55.760 --> 00:51:00.869
Because I know a lot of people who don't know.

00:51:16.400 --> 00:51:16.640
I don't know how you couldn't know.

00:51:19.966 --> 00:51:20.240
But okay, she's here.

00:51:20.240 --> 00:51:21.440
What the heck?

00:51:21.440 --> 00:51:21.920
Hi.

00:51:30.520 --> 00:51:30.820
I brought my friend here.

00:51:40.595 --> 00:51:40.853
I was just telling them about everything and walking in love and all that.

00:51:40.853 --> 00:51:43.520
They enjoy the Christmas lights.

00:51:43.520 --> 00:51:46.319
I don't know.

00:51:46.319 --> 00:51:47.520
I hope so.

00:51:47.520 --> 00:51:52.559
You know, we don't do that very often, but it's something fun.

00:51:54.800 --> 00:52:01.731
You want to take communion with me?

00:52:01.731 --> 00:52:08.555
Mhm.

00:52:18.800 --> 00:52:19.689
You can pray with me.

00:52:19.689 --> 00:52:27.211
Jesus, we sure love you, and we thank you, Father, for the days ahead.

00:52:27.211 --> 00:52:39.910
No matter how hard it is or how easy it is, we always give Jesus the glory.

00:52:49.866 --> 00:52:50.133
And we always keep him first.

00:52:50.133 --> 00:53:01.670
It's not always easy, but your flesh wants to be rebellious.

00:53:01.680 --> 00:53:05.190
It wants to act out, don't it?

00:53:05.190 --> 00:53:06.079
But God has made a way.

00:53:07.079 --> 00:53:16.800
And it's when you stay in the word, you got to get in the word.

00:53:16.800 --> 00:53:36.159
Father, we thank you for the body.

00:53:36.159 --> 00:53:42.720
We thank you, Father, for all these prayer warriors tonight, all 4,240 of them.

00:53:42.720 --> 00:54:07.611
Every person here tonight, Father, are so hungry and so desperate.

00:54:07.611 --> 00:54:27.119
It's in the middle of the night and they're here.

00:54:50.582 --> 00:54:51.085
Lord, I'm thankful, Father, for every person that's here tonight.

00:54:51.085 --> 00:54:55.279
I'm thankful for this congregation of people.

00:54:55.279 --> 00:55:14.227
Lord, we've even prayed over if we open up our own thing and have a building and open up our own little church and pray with the people more like that.

00:55:14.227 --> 00:55:24.773
We've been praying about it.

00:55:24.773 --> 00:55:51.760
I don't know if that's real wisdom for me because of people not liking me too much, but it's something that I have to really pray over.

00:55:51.760 --> 00:55:58.106
I'm not the most liked by some groups of people.

00:55:58.106 --> 00:56:05.280
So, it's not like having our pastors or whatever.

00:56:16.979 --> 00:56:17.359
It's not having a church like them.

00:56:17.359 --> 00:56:19.978
People don't hate them like they hate us.

00:56:34.000 --> 00:56:34.187
And it's not funny.

00:56:34.187 --> 00:56:39.704
People have developed an opinion about us, really.

00:56:39.704 --> 00:57:09.280
And there's a lot of you that love us and would go, but I'd have to have hired security continually.

00:57:09.280 --> 00:57:12.540
Armed security guards, armed police officers.

00:57:12.540 --> 00:58:28.720
I'd have to have several to have a meeting just to make sure the congregation was safe and Diana and I would remain safe.

00:58:44.480 --> 00:59:11.317
And so it's really something I'd have to really pray about because Diana and I talked about it last night and we would do it if he asked us to.

00:59:11.317 --> 00:59:31.071
Yeah, it's been on my heart because I like to pray live.

00:59:31.071 --> 01:01:00.360
It's amazing because there's a bigger pool, you know, whenever you're with a group of people and you can feel them.

01:01:00.360 --> 01:01:29.724
But it's putting yourself out there that you have security already and making sure they're armed and that there's no more incidences like Charlie Kirk, you know, and I don't want anybody to be in harm's way because of me and having a meeting.

01:01:29.724 --> 01:01:35.040
So, I would have to hire police officers or security.

01:01:35.040 --> 01:01:49.840
So, there's a lot more to us opening a building and having something in Tulsa.

01:02:57.680 --> 01:02:58.890
I would put it by ORU because of the college kids.

01:03:01.310 --> 01:03:06.150
I have a hunger.

01:03:06.160 --> 01:03:30.631
And so, there's just things that I have to pray about a lot.

01:04:47.620 --> 01:04:47.950
And security and being safe is a major deal for us, you know, because we have a lot of people that just don't like Brandon and Diana.

01:04:50.727 --> 01:04:51.103
And that's fine.

01:04:51.103 --> 01:04:54.666
But, Father, we thank you, Lord.

01:04:54.666 --> 01:04:57.280
We thank you, Lord.

01:04:57.280 --> 01:05:02.559
I had to say that as we're praying over that.

01:05:22.240 --> 01:05:22.560
And I, Father, I thank you, Lord, for your body.

01:05:22.560 --> 01:05:42.339
We thank you, Lord, for how much you love us and how much you've taken care of us.

01:05:42.339 --> 01:05:58.698
The blood of Jesus Christ covers us.

01:05:58.698 --> 01:06:13.977
We take this body in the name of Jesus.

01:06:13.977 --> 01:06:20.600
We thank you, Lord, that by your stripes, we're healed.

01:06:20.600 --> 01:06:28.139
You were wounded for our transgressions.

01:06:28.139 --> 01:06:35.598
You were bruised for our iniquities.

01:06:35.598 --> 01:06:50.137
The chastisement of our peace was upon you, and with your stripes, we are healed.

01:06:50.137 --> 01:06:59.314
Lord, Diana and I are walking in divine health.

01:06:59.314 --> 01:07:06.174
We're not beggars; we're believers.

01:07:06.174 --> 01:07:08.142
We believe we're overcomers.

01:07:08.142 --> 01:07:33.348
We believe, Father, that everyone watching right now is healed, whole, and well by the stripes of Jesus.

01:07:33.348 --> 01:07:46.879
You walk in divine health like the little boy we prayed for who had cancer and was completely healed.

01:08:04.837 --> 01:08:05.536
We believe, Father, that you're no respecter of persons, and what you do for him, you'll do for them.

01:08:05.536 --> 01:08:54.285
Tonight, we believe that their expiration date for what they're believing for is today.

01:08:54.285 --> 01:08:57.119
Today they're overcomers.

01:08:57.119 --> 01:09:12.870
Today they're healed.

01:09:12.880 --> 01:09:18.852
Today they're whole.

01:09:18.852 --> 01:09:20.586
Today they're well.

01:09:34.959 --> 01:09:35.259
Father, they walk in divine healing and health.

01:09:35.259 --> 01:09:52.159
We thank you, Lord, for the body that was broken for us, and we take it in the mighty name of Jesus.

01:09:52.159 --> 01:09:52.958
Amen.

01:09:52.958 --> 01:09:55.870
Lord, we thank you for the blood.

01:10:09.600 --> 01:10:10.093
We make much of the blood, and the blood makes much of us.

01:10:10.093 --> 01:10:32.684
We apply the blood of Jesus from the top of our heads to the soles of our feet, so that we always stay in the right way, at the right place, at the right time.

01:10:32.684 --> 01:11:32.343
We're always in the right place at the right time doing exactly what you called us to do.

01:11:32.343 --> 01:11:59.312
We're never caught off guard.

01:11:59.312 --> 01:12:11.348
If you say don't go, we don't go.

01:12:11.348 --> 01:12:14.959
If you say go, we go.

01:12:14.959 --> 01:12:17.520
We flow with love.

01:12:17.520 --> 01:12:23.520
Father, we ooze love; that's who we are.

01:12:23.520 --> 01:12:25.559
We're just like Jesus.

01:12:25.559 --> 01:12:31.420
Regardless, we walk in love and we plead the blood over sin.

01:12:31.420 --> 01:12:37.840
We close doors that we've opened and plead the blood over those doors.

01:12:37.840 --> 01:12:43.510
We ask for mercy.

01:12:43.520 --> 01:12:44.880
Lord, have mercy on us.

01:12:46.729 --> 01:13:21.830
I thank you, Lord, regardless of whatever it is in our lives, we confess our sins, and you said you are faithful and just to forgive us and cleanse us from all unrighteousness.

01:13:21.840 --> 01:13:37.040
I plead the blood over Diana from the top of her head to the soles of her feet.

01:13:37.040 --> 01:14:09.298
We thank you, Lord, for whom the Son has set free is free indeed.

01:14:09.298 --> 01:14:18.880
We're blessed in the city and in the field, coming in and going out in the name of Jesus.

01:14:18.880 --> 01:14:22.857
Father, we plead the blood.

01:14:22.857 --> 01:14:30.856
I thank you that we are uninterrupted and unhindered by any satanic or demonic force.

01:14:30.856 --> 01:14:44.320
Father, I thank you that you speak through my vocal cords and think through my mind—all of you and none of me.

01:14:44.320 --> 01:14:58.873
Father, I plead the blood over my spiritual eyes.

01:14:58.873 --> 01:15:48.709
If there's anything you want to show us tonight in prayer, we come boldly into your throne room.

01:16:18.270 --> 01:16:18.540
I thank you, Lord, that you show us that which is to come.

01:16:18.540 --> 01:16:57.280
We have eyes to see and ears to hear, for we will hear your voice and a stranger's voice we will not follow.

01:16:57.280 --> 01:17:52.719
We will hear and see clearly, and we will not be snared by any satanic or demonic force.

01:17:52.719 --> 01:18:15.920
In Jesus' name, amen.

01:18:31.480 --> 01:18:31.840
That was different tonight, but I had to do something different because I felt something.

01:18:31.840 --> 01:18:35.627
What are you going to say?

01:18:59.627 --> 01:19:00.133
You okay?

01:19:01.653 --> 01:19:02.353
You touched it.

01:19:02.353 --> 01:19:03.520
Yeah, I saw that.

01:19:03.520 --> 01:19:05.720
It dumped out.

01:19:17.520 --> 01:19:17.840
You can dump some of that on your hand.

01:19:17.840 --> 01:19:18.857
I'm okay.

01:19:18.857 --> 01:19:19.989
All right.

01:19:19.989 --> 01:19:21.876
Who wants to go tubing?

01:19:21.876 --> 01:19:28.370
I know most of you want to go tubing, but I always ask.

01:19:28.370 --> 01:19:29.360
It's fun.

01:19:29.360 --> 01:19:31.099
It's time to work.

01:19:32.849 --> 01:19:34.410
You ready to go to work?

01:19:34.410 --> 01:19:37.600
Father, we worship you.

01:19:37.600 --> 01:19:43.920
We thank you, Lord, for how good you have been to us.

01:19:43.920 --> 01:20:06.267
You've been good to Brandon Biggs, to my wife, and to my kids.

01:20:06.267 --> 01:20:09.259
We're so thankful for all you've done.

01:20:09.259 --> 01:20:13.360
We apply the blood of Jesus and we make much of it.

01:20:13.360 --> 01:20:21.126
Father, it never loses its power.

01:20:36.056 --> 01:20:36.434
It reaches to the highest mountain and flows to the lowest valley.

01:20:36.434 --> 01:20:40.700
Your blood cleanses us and makes us whole.

01:20:46.928 --> 01:20:47.176
It washes over us in the name of Jesus.

01:20:48.180 --> 01:20:52.887
The blood that gives me strength from day to day will never lose its power.

01:20:53.536 --> 01:21:04.067
It reaches to the highest mountain and flows to the lowest valley.

01:21:15.675 --> 01:21:32.800
The blood that Jesus shed for me way back on Calvary, the blood that gives me strength from day to day, will never lose its power.

01:21:32.800 --> 01:21:37.387
Father, we thank you for the blood.

01:21:37.387 --> 01:21:39.484
Your blood is sufficient for me.

01:21:43.024 --> 01:21:43.248
What can wash away my sin?

01:21:43.248 --> 01:21:49.590
Nothing but the blood of Jesus.

01:21:49.600 --> 01:21:53.919
What can make me whole again?

01:21:53.919 --> 01:21:59.263
Nothing but the blood of Jesus.

01:21:59.263 --> 01:22:09.927
Precious is the flow that makes me white as snow.

01:22:09.927 --> 01:22:17.040
No other fount I know, nothing but the blood of Jesus.

01:22:17.040 --> 01:22:30.149
Thank you, Father, for the blood.

01:22:30.149 --> 01:22:34.596
Thank you that it never loses its power.

01:22:34.596 --> 01:22:38.480
We're coming up higher to the fire.

01:22:38.480 --> 01:22:42.192
We're coming up by your side.

01:22:42.192 --> 01:23:29.440
I thank you, Lord, that we're drawn by your side and we're walking with you on a day-to-day basis.

01:23:40.103 --> 01:23:40.389
The glory of the Lord rests on us.

01:23:40.389 --> 01:24:02.835
There are many of you that need to forgive people that have hurt you.

01:24:02.835 --> 01:24:08.760
Just say it: 'I forgive them.

01:24:08.760 --> 01:24:12.069
' Walk in love.

01:24:12.069 --> 01:24:14.520
I forgive so-and-so.

01:24:14.520 --> 01:24:18.400
I forgive them by faith.

01:24:18.400 --> 01:24:27.440
Love takes no account of a suffered wrong.

01:24:27.440 --> 01:24:30.147
Be quick to forgive.

01:24:30.147 --> 01:24:56.960
Don't hold a grudge; it builds a dam in your heart.

01:24:56.960 --> 01:25:10.870
Don't allow strife and evil works to build a dam in your heart.

01:25:10.880 --> 01:25:36.336
Let the love of God flow freely inside of you like a river.

01:25:48.992 --> 01:25:52.959
It doesn't mean you have to let people keep hurting you, but don't let strife and anger keep that love from walking out of you.

01:25:52.959 --> 01:26:03.546
Just release it and let it go.

01:26:03.546 --> 01:26:05.560
Does that make sense?

01:26:05.560 --> 01:26:17.320
Many of you have taken offense at people even at church, at work, or at school.

01:26:17.320 --> 01:26:24.708
You've let them build a stronghold of bitterness inside of you.

01:26:24.708 --> 01:26:32.725
Tonight, the Lord wants you to let it go.

01:26:32.725 --> 01:26:35.520
Let the Holy Ghost flow.

01:26:35.520 --> 01:26:50.217
When you keep anger and bitterness inside of you, it brings a dam.

01:26:50.217 --> 01:26:55.287
Out of your belly shall flow rivers of living water.

01:26:55.287 --> 01:26:57.208
Love never fails.

01:26:57.208 --> 01:27:06.400
I have to talk to myself like this all the time.

01:27:06.400 --> 01:27:09.120
Shut up, flesh!

01:27:09.120 --> 01:27:11.120
Love never fails.

01:27:11.120 --> 01:27:19.120
I am rooted and grounded in love.

01:27:19.120 --> 01:27:39.740
Thank you, Father, for the Holy Ghost, for he will help you.

01:27:39.740 --> 01:27:52.070
They did me wrong with finances or a business deal.

01:27:52.080 --> 01:28:04.960
They ripped me off.

01:28:04.960 --> 01:28:31.193
They did this.

01:28:31.193 --> 01:28:51.990
They did that.

01:28:52.000 --> 01:29:29.382
You keep holding on to grudges.

01:29:29.382 --> 01:30:04.810
Well, she was a bad wife in my first marriage, boy, and I tell you what, I hope she burns and rots in hell.

01:30:04.810 --> 01:30:10.800
I mean, seriously, right?

01:30:32.773 --> 01:30:33.147
And so you build that up inside and you've got that bitterness.

01:30:33.147 --> 01:31:09.940
You had a bad divorce—and we know some people had some bad divorces—and 40 years later, they're still holding it.

01:31:09.940 --> 01:31:33.214
30 years later, they're still holding it.

01:32:00.450 --> 01:32:00.760
You mention their name and they tremble; that's cancer.

01:32:01.070 --> 01:32:24.310
You don't want that in your life.

01:32:24.320 --> 01:32:27.720
I forgive them.

01:32:27.720 --> 01:32:48.390
My grandmother was like that.

01:32:48.400 --> 01:33:33.230
She had a very bad, abusive marriage the first time when she was young.

01:33:33.230 --> 01:34:10.297
My grandfather was very abusive and she carried that for the rest of her life and she died early.

01:34:10.297 --> 01:34:13.584
She got cancer and died.

01:34:13.584 --> 01:34:44.833
Bitterness is a cancer and you've got to let things go.

01:34:44.833 --> 01:35:23.025
My grandmother held that on there and every time you talked about them, she would get a snarl in her mouth.

01:35:23.025 --> 01:36:36.693
She'd just look at them like she wanted to spit.

01:36:36.693 --> 01:38:05.520
And I'm talking, they were divorced for years and she was married to another man and had kids by him and everything was fine.

01:38:05.977 --> 01:38:11.632
You would think so, but she took it into the next marriage.

01:38:19.074 --> 01:38:20.045
So I'm trying to tell you this: Don't take your drama from your last into the next.

01:38:22.720 --> 01:38:25.600
You may be here tonight and you're getting ready to get married.

01:38:25.600 --> 01:38:55.310
You've already been married before and you have bitterness towards your husband or wife and there's something eating at you still, but you're about to take it into your next marriage.

01:38:55.310 --> 01:39:14.480
You're about to take it into your next relationship.

01:39:19.960 --> 01:39:20.880
It cannot go with you.

01:39:20.880 --> 01:39:22.933
Leave the dirty laundry out.

01:39:22.933 --> 01:39:26.800
Leave the garbage out.

01:39:26.800 --> 01:40:19.635
Don't take it into the next one.

01:40:19.635 --> 01:40:32.120
Then people leave churches.

01:40:32.120 --> 01:40:48.400
They get offended.

01:40:48.400 --> 01:41:15.462
And then you go, 'Well, I'm leaving.

01:41:15.462 --> 01:41:22.149
I'm mad.

01:41:22.159 --> 01:41:31.990
I'm out of here.

01:41:32.000 --> 01:41:48.560
' And they take that offense and that bitterness into the next church.

01:41:48.560 --> 01:42:03.139
I've seen it time and time again when we worked at the church.

01:42:11.199 --> 01:42:13.834
We were there for years.

01:42:20.159 --> 01:42:21.439
And people—Sister Clipboard was all upset.

01:42:21.439 --> 01:44:10.620
She'd come in there with her list of clipboard issues and she would get mad and stay for five years or five months and she's out of there because she's upset and bitter.

01:44:10.620 --> 01:44:11.719
Did something happen?

01:44:11.719 --> 01:44:12.159
Okay.

01:44:12.159 --> 01:44:18.160
So, you've got to learn to let it go.

01:44:18.160 --> 01:44:20.948
Be like Elsa.

01:44:20.948 --> 01:44:26.573
Like, 'Let it go, let it go.

01:44:26.573 --> 01:44:31.013
' I was playing it on Christmas Day.

01:44:31.013 --> 01:44:36.159
'Let it go, let it go, let it go.

01:44:36.159 --> 01:44:37.439
' Hallelujah.

01:44:37.439 --> 01:44:41.119
You've got to let it go.

01:44:41.119 --> 01:45:13.472
I don't know if that ministers to anybody, but it's just in my spirit, I guess, because it's on the topic.

01:45:13.472 --> 01:45:40.720
Don't take it into your next marriage.

01:45:40.720 --> 01:45:47.253
Especially, I see a woman—I just saw a vision right then.

01:46:00.880 --> 01:46:01.794
And I see the woman: You're getting ready to get married.

01:46:16.560 --> 01:46:16.836
It's going to be a new transition in your life come January of 2026 around this time frame.

01:46:20.949 --> 01:46:21.337
And you're about to get married come the spring.

01:46:24.720 --> 01:46:26.996
And the Lord's showing me that you just left not even a year ago.

01:46:26.996 --> 01:46:30.251
Might be a little longer.

01:46:30.251 --> 01:46:31.644
A year.

01:46:33.031 --> 01:46:34.418
I see the window.

01:46:34.880 --> 01:47:06.666
It's like a calendar passing like this, but the arrows are going backwards, not forwards.

01:47:06.666 --> 01:47:27.227
They're going backwards and you're going back to the divorce court and the bitterness is still eating you alive.

01:47:34.919 --> 01:47:38.731
I see the arrow and the months passing behind like you're rewinding in slow motion.

01:47:39.246 --> 01:47:49.279
This is rewinding in slow motion in front of my eyes right now.

01:47:51.520 --> 01:48:05.320
And I see it all moving back and you are so, so bitter still.

01:48:17.440 --> 01:48:26.719
And the Lord tells me this next marriage won't last very long if you don't bring it to my throne.

01:48:26.719 --> 01:48:44.157
You must bring this to my throne or the next marriage won't last very long.

01:48:44.157 --> 01:49:09.750
You even wear your hair up in a twist sometimes with braids.

01:49:09.760 --> 01:49:25.360
I see this braid running down in the back right here.

01:50:46.239 --> 01:50:46.819
There's like a braid coming here.

01:50:58.640 --> 01:50:58.933
And you're a very prim and proper person.

01:50:58.933 --> 01:51:01.720
You're very structured, very detailed.

01:51:41.553 --> 01:51:41.908
You do the same pattern a lot every single day.

01:51:45.234 --> 01:51:47.640
You know who I'm talking to.

01:51:47.640 --> 01:51:52.560
You take care of your flesh.

01:51:52.560 --> 01:51:59.589
You're very structured.

01:51:59.599 --> 01:52:15.457
And your husband was a pretty good businessman in your last marriage.

01:52:30.639 --> 01:52:33.370
I can even see your kitchen and the way your cabinets are and how this is all set up in there.

01:52:51.460 --> 01:52:52.230
You had a very big argument in that kitchen.

01:53:00.126 --> 01:53:00.469
The Lord wants to turn that sorrow into joy.

01:53:00.469 --> 01:53:06.649
He wants to turn the sorrow, the grieving, the grieving.

01:53:45.547 --> 01:53:45.920
There's great grieving.

01:53:45.920 --> 01:53:50.400
Let it go.

01:53:50.400 --> 01:53:53.679
Let it go.

01:53:53.679 --> 01:54:06.977
You're even upset with how much you didn't get in the divorce.

01:54:10.960 --> 01:54:48.586
You felt you should have gotten a lot more and you have bitterness even by that.

01:54:48.586 --> 01:55:07.920
'I should have gotten more at the court.

01:55:07.920 --> 01:55:41.006
I should have gotten more at that divorce.

01:55:41.006 --> 01:55:48.759
' Harmony, you must stop this.

01:56:38.399 --> 01:56:38.759
I hear the spirit of the Lord say you must stop this.

01:56:46.719 --> 01:56:47.279
He has more.

01:57:21.600 --> 01:57:22.000
This will be the most joyous time of restoring what the cankerworm ate in your life.

01:57:22.000 --> 01:57:30.274
You will have the most joyous time if you don't take this into the next relationship.

01:57:31.136 --> 01:57:34.320
There's great peace and joy.

01:57:48.480 --> 01:57:51.180
The Lord's wanting to restore you.

01:57:51.180 --> 01:58:05.109
Yeah, he cheated.

01:58:05.119 --> 01:58:07.040
Yeah, those things happened.

01:58:07.040 --> 01:58:10.559
Yeah, you have pain.

01:58:10.559 --> 01:58:12.817
Yeah, you're hurting.

01:58:12.817 --> 01:58:14.239
Let it go.

01:58:14.239 --> 01:58:16.010
Walk with love.

01:58:16.010 --> 01:58:21.070
Many more days He has in store for you.

01:58:21.070 --> 01:58:23.296
Joy, joy, joy.

01:58:23.296 --> 01:58:26.480
Hurry, let it go.

01:58:35.093 --> 01:58:35.387
Don't let him take up any more space in your mind.

01:58:35.387 --> 01:58:38.410
No, make sure it's left behind.

01:58:38.410 --> 01:58:42.196
Don't take it into the next one.

01:59:00.139 --> 01:59:01.080
That was amazing.

01:59:22.586 --> 01:59:24.986
I don't know your name, but I saw you and the Lord has great plans for you.

01:59:24.986 --> 01:59:29.280
I'm excited for you.

01:59:32.337 --> 01:59:40.519
It's not going to be easy to the flesh, but you do it by faith.

01:59:40.519 --> 01:59:45.867
'I forgive him.

02:00:00.159 --> 02:00:00.479
I forgive him, Lord.

02:00:01.440 --> 02:00:02.080
I release it.

02:00:02.080 --> 02:00:20.680
I'm so thankful you brought this new man to me.

02:00:20.680 --> 02:00:29.920
' He's going to be a good man, a good friend, a good companion.

02:00:52.097 --> 02:00:52.346
And I'm not going to take the trash from my past into my future.

02:00:52.346 --> 02:00:55.040
So, whoever that was for, bless you.

02:00:55.040 --> 02:00:57.611
Father, I thank you, Lord.

02:00:57.611 --> 02:00:58.605
Two divorces.

02:00:58.605 --> 02:01:00.221
Pain, pain, pain.

02:01:02.089 --> 02:01:02.880
The Lord said, 'Leave that there.

02:01:02.880 --> 02:01:04.418
' Thank you, Lord.

02:01:04.418 --> 02:01:06.106
Glory to God.

02:01:06.106 --> 02:01:07.599
In Jesus' name.

02:01:07.599 --> 02:01:08.080
Wonderful.

02:01:08.080 --> 02:01:11.928
Now, let's go down this other road.

02:01:11.928 --> 02:01:13.920
Father, we thank you, Lord.

02:01:34.756 --> 02:01:35.031
I sit here and I'll wait.

02:01:35.582 --> 02:01:38.839
I don't know what direction to go after that.

02:01:38.839 --> 02:01:40.039
It's in the Caribbean.

02:01:40.039 --> 02:01:42.763
An escalation.

02:01:44.026 --> 02:01:49.872
I see coming out of the water.

02:01:51.613 --> 02:01:52.947
I feel the heat from it.

02:02:09.040 --> 02:02:09.390
I feel the heat from Soldado Bay from the explosion on that bay.

02:02:09.390 --> 02:02:13.550
Do you remember what Saddam did to the oil wells?

02:02:13.550 --> 02:02:20.709
Do you remember what Saddam did to the oil wells before the Persian Gulf War?

02:02:20.709 --> 02:02:26.560
Remember what he did to those wells?

02:02:26.560 --> 02:02:32.478
He set them on fire and he burnt them.

02:02:32.478 --> 02:02:45.599
He booby-trapped them, making it where we couldn't come in and get the oil.

02:02:45.599 --> 02:02:48.183
Do you remember this?

02:02:48.183 --> 02:02:52.639
Watch this.

02:02:52.639 --> 02:02:54.286
Watch the oil wells.

02:02:54.286 --> 02:02:56.060
Watch the oil derricks.

02:02:56.060 --> 02:03:12.1000
Watch the oil wells as an escalation at the shore, at sea as an invasion, as a last resort.

02:03:12.1000 --> 02:03:14.080
It's mysterious.

02:03:43.152 --> 02:03:43.728
I see the jungle.

02:03:46.259 --> 02:03:58.600
I see these devices on these oil rigs.

02:03:58.600 --> 02:04:16.788
I see all the smoke in the sky.

02:04:16.788 --> 02:04:17.937
Focus, focus.

02:04:17.937 --> 02:04:19.982
Oh, that's interesting.

02:04:19.982 --> 02:04:31.660
I've never seen anything like that before.

02:04:31.660 --> 02:04:39.146
It's like a stinger on a tail.

02:04:39.146 --> 02:04:54.139
It's like a point of this claw, and there's a stinger in the middle of it.

02:04:54.719 --> 02:04:58.170
It looks like a green, lizard-looking tail.

02:04:58.170 --> 02:05:13.360
It comes out, there are scales on it, and at the tip of this green thing, there's a ball.

02:05:13.360 --> 02:05:19.679
There's a ball on the tip of this that has claws on the side.

02:05:19.679 --> 02:05:28.639
Four claws coming up on a green shaft with scales on this ball with a red tip.

02:05:28.639 --> 02:05:35.599
